dictweb1913:
"'
Devitrification \De*vit`ri*fi*ca"tion\, n.
   The conversion of molten glassy matter into a stony mass by slow cooling, the result being the formation of crystallites, microbites, etc., in the glassy base, which are then called devitrification products.
'"

Solar mirrors melt sand while artisans blow glass.
